{"type":"message","id":"1642c64e","parentId":"aa336851","timestamp":"2026-06-10T07:19:39.012Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The claw clip product (25395566794) is:\n- Shop: LASSY, a preferred shop in Hanoi\n- Price: 17,600 VND (~$0.70)\n- Brand: NOVSET\n- Rating: 4.88\n- 上架时间: 2025-06-14 (relatively new - about 1 year)\n- Monthly sales: 961, 7D: 0 (7 day sales is 0 because it was recently corrected)\n\nThe price is still too low for our $1.5+ threshold.\n\n\nI'm realizing the market reality here—Vietnam's price ceiling for hair clips is around $0.4-$2.0, which makes hitting the $1.50 minimum price point and 70% gross margin simultaneously very difficult with a single item. Maybe I should reconsider the approach and look at a premium claw clip set instead.\n\nLooking at the TikTok data, the SÂU HOUSE 6-tooth claw clip at 49,000 VND (~$1.96) with 4.8 stars and 17,431 reviews is performing really well with 1,140 weekly sales. At that price point with a 1688 cost around $0.30-0.50, the gross margin lands around 181% after the 45% operating cost, which clears the 70% threshold comfortably. But since the 1688 search came up empty, I need to pivot and find the actual TikTok Vietnam product link for this item to verify it properly. Now I'm pulling the product details from TikTok for the SÂU HOUSE claw clip items to verify pricing and get the shop information, then I'll check if there's a complementary listing that shows the buy-one-get-one deal. I'm continuing to pull the product details from TikTok—the next item is a floral hair clip with a rating of 4.6 stars and over 22,000 reviews, priced at 10,500 VND with weekly sales around 1,130 units. I'm compiling the product data from TikTok and now I need to verify the 1688 pricing for the top performer—the claw clip set that's moving 1,140 units weekly at 49,000 VND—to calculate whether it meets the margin requirements.\n\nThe price point of ~$1.96 is actually workable for Vietnam, but since the 1688 search didn't return results, I should pivot to finding a reliable supplier link directly rather than continuing with the search.\n","thinkingSignature":"70dc39f037670c71ba6c3e4ea4679f52ff37f52f04ed25c2d9b9a7e6af5285f5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4f3d0ba737ec4b6a8fd68b1e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST 'https://mcp.sorftime.com/' \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $(cat /tmp/sorftime_key.txt)\" \\\n  -H 'accept: application/json, text/event-stream' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"tools/call\",\"params\":{\"name\":\"tiktok_product_detail\",\"arguments\":{\"productId\":\"1732311961339659361\",\"site\":\"VN\"}},\"id\":12}'"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0c4825afe2aa4270aa6de0c7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -X POST 'https://mcp.sorftime.com/' \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $(cat /tmp/sorftime_key.txt)\" \\\n  -H 'accept: application/json, text/event-stream' \\\n  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n  -d '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"tools/call\",\"params\":{\"name\":\"tiktok_product_detail\",\"arguments\":{\"productId\":\"17329850600634812513\",\"site\":\"VN\"}},\"id\":13}'"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":963,"output":767,"cacheRead":122848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124578,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781075970761,"responseId":"06784303675166a6b580b3fa88fdea06"}}
